<subSubSection pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[200,323,187,212]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Maxilla 1 palp constricted. Gnathopod 1 propodus palm strongly serrate. Gnathopod 2 basis with well-developed anterodistal lobe; propodus posterior margin subquadrate; dactylus short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis box="[201,661,260,284]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,288,260,284]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Female</emphasis>
(sexually dimorphic characters).
</emphasis>
Gnathopod 2 basis is not expanded anteriorly, the propodus is more oval-shaped, and the dactylus is thinner than in males.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,151,428]" box="[201,551,331,356]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,300,331,356]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" reason="1">Habitat.</emphasis>
